prompt: If Snarfloon(x,y) and Frooblenap(y,z) then what are the possible relationships between x and z?
answer:
Snarfloon(x,y) means x and y share only a boundary (no interior), and Frooblenap(y,z) means y and z are coincident (they occupy exactly the same region). If y and z are the same region, then x shares only a boundary with y exactly if x shares only a boundary with z. Hence the only possible relationship between x and z is Snarfloon(x,z).

### Answer: Snarfloon(x,z)
